@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/health

###

### ─────────────────────────────────────────
### URL — receive JSON with link, download + transcribe (no DB needed)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────

### Transcribe from URL (sent by n8n or another service)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/transcribe/url
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "type": "audio",
  "link": "https://n8n.dsliked.work.gd/api/recordings/file?path=2026%2F04-April%2Faudio%2FRoom_2_Chris_Brian_P_2026-04-22_15-08-56.wav",
  "fileName": "Room_2_Chris_Brian_P_2026-04-22_15-08-56.wav",
  "relativePath": "2026/04-April/audio/Room_2_Chris_Brian_P_2026-04-22_15-08-56.wav",
  "roomName": "Room 2",
  "botName": null,
  "participants": ["Chris","Clive", "Elion", "Brian P"],
  "durationSeconds": 1097.377,
  "sizeBytes": 35116032,
  "meetingId": "5096021684",
  "completedAt": "2026-04-23T08:56:26.473Z"
}

###

### ─────────────────────────────────────────
### SYNC — upload file directly, no DB needed
### ─────────────────────────────────────────

### Upload .wav file (sync — returns transcript immediately)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/transcribe/sync
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="audio.wav"
Content-Type: audio/wav

< ./audio.wav
--boundary--

###

### ─────────────────────────────────────────
### ASYNC — queue + Supabase job tracking
### ─────────────────────────────────────────

### Upload .wav file (async — returns jobId, poll for result)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/transcribe
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="audio.wav"
Content-Type: audio/wav

< ./audio.wav
--boundary--

###

### Set jobId from async response then use below
@jobId = JOB_ID

### Check job status
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/jobs/{{jobId}}

###

### Get transcript result
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/jobs/{{jobId}}/result

###

### List all jobs
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/jobs
